Package com.northeastern.labyrinth.Model.Board

Class Tile

java.lang.Object
com.northeastern.labyrinth.Model.Board.Tile
public final class Tile extends Object
Represents a tile as a invalid input: '<'Direction, Boolean> Map that represents which Tiles it connects to. The map always has 4 entries each corresponding to a value in the Direction enum. Example for â”” Tile: invalid input: '<'UP, true> invalid input: '<'LEFT, false> invalid input: '<'DOWN, false> invalid input: '<'RIGHT, true> Each Tile also has a unique, unordered combination of two gems that can be used to identify a specific Tile.

    • rotateClockwise

      public Tile rotateClockwise(int degrees) throws IllegalArgumentException
      Rotates a tile counter-clockwise by the given degree.
      Parameters:
      degrees - int representing a degree of rotation. Negative represents clockwise movement.
      Returns:
      A new copy with the applied rotation to the connector Map.
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if given degrees is not a multiple of 90.
